DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Inhibin B Outcome Upper Limit of Normal Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the upper limit of normal numeric value for the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for inhibin B.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information relating to the result of a laboratory procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for inhibin B (a hormone produced by the follicle cells of the ovary and by the Sertoli and Ledig cells of testis).

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: Inhibin B, consisting of an alpha subunit and a beta B subunit linked by disulphide bonds, is a heterodimer hormone produced by the follicle cells of the ovary and by the Sertoli and Ledig cells of testis.  Although other forms of inhibin also exist in men, inhibin B is the predominant form in the circulation in men.:The result of an action.

Concepts.definition: Inhibin B, consisting of an alpha subunit and a beta B subunit linked by disulphide bonds, is a heterodimer hormone produced by the follicle cells of the ovary and by the Sertoli and Ledig cells of testis.  Although other forms of inhibin also exist in men, inhibin B is the predominant form in the circulation in men.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: the numerical quantity for the top value of the range of statistical characteristics that are supposed to represent an accepted standard, non-pathological pattern for a particular laboratory result or other quantitative parameter.
